* SIM Swaps
.background images/GOOGLE-02.png
- Not an issue in Malaysia as far as we know
- Somebody call telco support, claims new phone
- Gets phone number ported to new phone
- hack your email using SMS as recovery method
- hack anything else with email & SMS fallbacks

* Asian Scams
.background images/GOOGLE-02.png
- Spend a LOT on marketing
- Have wallets with 99% credible currencies and one oddball
- Promote a lot but explain very little
- Multiple angles in it for the owners
- Usually base much of their business outside their target countries
- employ MLM methods
- target the vulnerable
- love glitzy events (implying affluence by participation)
- want to take photos with VIPS (credibility by association)

* What can we do about it ?
.background images/GOOGLE-02.png
- Education in ALL media
- Industry associations
- Teach financial prudence / literacy
- Improve enforcement

If *YOU* have a project
- establish your credibility
- put business first
- be as transparent as possible
- allow people to verify everything
